subject: [Important] Your 1st Quarter Payroll Tax Reconciliation is Complete
body:
Hi,
Reconciliation runs are part of a payroll provider's normal quarter's-end reconciliation process. Payroll is running those corrections to ensure you pay the correct amount to each tax jurisdiction where you're liable for payroll taxes.
When we do reconciliations, we look for variances between what we collected in taxes from your pay runs in the quarter and what the tax agencies expect you to pay. In some cases, we'll find variances between these two amounts. Variances are normal, and can be the result of a number of things.
Here's a snapshot of where you stand, and what will happen next:
For your Full-Service jurisdictions, we will automatically create pay runs in your account and you'll see the following net amount 
credited to 
your bank account ending in ******6303 by April 07, 2025 for $0.05 for Unemployment Tax.
For additional details, please feel free to review your 
Tax Payments report
 from your Payroll app.
Thanks, 
TriNet 
Questions or concerns? Visit 
help.zenefits.com
. 
© TriNet

subject: Email 1: Your Insurance Audit Is Due
body:
Complete Your Insurance Audit Soon 
 
 
 
 
LANGUAGE CULTURE WORLDWIDE 
Policy Number: 83 WEC AR3HC0
 
It’s time once again to complete your insurance audit that’s required for your policy. You have until 
May 6 2025
 to submit it. 
 
Start Your Audit Now
 
 
 
 
 
 
Here’s What You’ll Need 
 
For Payroll‑Based Policies (Workers’ Comp or Property/Liability): 
 
 
☐ 
 
Payroll tax documents, such as IRS forms 941 or 944, or state unemployment returns. (We prefer you use form 941. However, if you don’t have your most recent 941, you can still get started.)
 
 
☐ 
 
A payroll report with wages by employee for the policy period. 
 
 
☐ 
 
Names of owners and officers, and a breakdown of their ownership percentages. 
 
 
☐ 
 
Names, amounts paid, and insurance information for subcontractors and temporary/leased workers. 
 
For Sales‑Based Policies (Property/Liability): 
 
 
☐ 
 
A sales report that details your gross sales during your policy period. 
 
 
☐ 
 
A Profit and Loss Statement (P&L) or an Income Statement. 
 
 
☐ 
 
If you don’t have a P&L or Income Statement then we’ll need your most recently filed business tax return. 
 
 
 
 
 
 
Reminder of Why You Have to Complete an Audit 
 
Audits are required for a couple reasons. First, your policy requires us to perform an insurance audit to meet our contractual obligations, and in most states, it’s the law. Secondly, it gives you the opportunity to make sure what you paid for your policy matched the risks you had while it covered you. So, think of it as your policy checkup. Plus, doing the audit can help you avoid a significant fine–up to three times the amount of your original policy premium, depending on your state’s rules. 
 
 
 
 
 
Have Questions About Your Audit? 
 
Give us a call at 
1‑866‑467‑8730
, weekdays between 8:00 a.m. and 8:00 p.m. ET. We're here to help.

subject: RE: Prepayment of comp question
body:
Hi Chuck – I think the main error is that this was 4 pay periods, not 3.
 
The way I calculated the off-cycle pay run was to put in the number of hours for 4 pay periods, and your rate is the same as it has been. Zenefits calculated the taxes and auto-filled your 401k contributions, and I manually updated the insurance deductions to 4x their last amount.
 
Your net pay on this run was $12,990.76 (covering 2 months of work, March 2 thru May 1). For the previous single period (Feb 15 thru March 1) your net pay was $3,615.80, which is a bit more than ¼ of what was just paid. The difference comes in the income tax withholding, they held back a larger percentage of the advance check than usual. I’m not sure how that’s calculated, and I can’t override it, but if it’s an overage it will come back in your refund next year.
 
Details of the advance run are below, and the previous one is below that for comparison.
 
Advance run 3/19/25
 
 
 
Regular run 3/14/25
 
 
 
From:
 Chuck Adams <c.adams@lcwmail.com> 
Sent:
 Monday, March 24, 2025 15:36
To:
 Sarah Gluckstein <s.gluckstein@lcwmail.com>
Subject:
 Prepayment of comp question
 
Hi.
 
My wife was doing math and it looks like if you divide the amount of the prepayment across 3 pay periods it comes to $4,330.25 per. That is ~$700 more a pay period than I was getting at the 30% reduction. Is there something we are  missing?
 
Chuck

subject: Please fill out this AR Analysis
body:
Please fill this out. There are three tabs
Summary – this will pull AR info from AR tab and deposit info from deposit tab to show the collectability of customer AR
AR aging – import AR as of today and complete columns
 
G:J
Type – should be one of below unless
 
I am missing one
                 
 
i.
     
 
Finished: invoice for completed services that should be collected
                
 
ii.
     
 
Deposit: invoice for deposit on account
              
 
iii.
     
 
Milestone: invoice for partially completed work. Also known as WIP.
Deposit on hand – this is to note whether or not this customer has a deposit on hand.
Collectible – simply note if there are any issues with the receivable. If it’s good AR, list it at 100%. If it’s disputed or prepayment, lower the collectability to 0-50%.
Deposits
 
It’d be helpful to get the below (with as much detail as possible)
AR aging
Deposit list
 
Note:
Is the AR for finished / completed work
Does the customer have any deposits on hand
 
Please layout the AR and match deposits. This is an AR analysis.
Thanks,
Alisa

subject: Spring into BILL updates 🌼
body:
See what’s new at BILL: BILL Procurement, 1099 corrections, side-by-side invoice view, become a BILL champion, and more.
  
 
 
 
 
1099 corrections
BILL now simplifies the tedious process of generating accurate corrections, ensuring compliance with IRS regulations, and filing those corrected 1099s to the IRS.
If you still haven't filed your 1099s, it isn't too late to do so in BILL!
  
  
FILE TODAY
 
  
  
 
 
Coming soon: 
BILL Procurement (Beta)
Get ready for a simpler way to manage procurement! BILL Procurement empowers businesses to extend control and visibility across procure-to-pay workflows, streamlining processes from a single, easy-to-use workspace.
Create purchase requests in BILL and route them for approval based on policies you set.
Send approved purchase orders to vendors.
Automate matching between the purchase order and invoices using powerful AI and automation from BILL.
Keep an eye out for launch updates!
  
  
 
 
Become a BILL Champion
Your voice matters. Share your wins, make connections, and build the future of finance with us.
The BILL Champions Program puts your story front and center. You’ll join a dynamic community of thought leaders driving innovation in financial operations—all while spotlighting your unique journey and achievements.
Showcase your strengths through co-marketing opportunities, including events, speaking engagements, brand sponsorships, and more.
  
  
JOIN NOW
 
  
  
 
 
Share your self-shot videos
Something exciting is launching soon 👀. We're looking for self-shot videos of your real-life stories, experiences, and results of being a BILL customer—and yes, there will be incentives. Fill out this short Google form to get early access to this exclusive customer campaign.
  
  
SIGN UP NOW
 
  
  
 
 
International Payments: view invoices side-by-side when adding a vendor
Adding a new vendor? Upload your invoices into a side-by-side view while you're adding a new vendor. Easily view the full name, address, phone number, and other necessary details to accurately add and pay your international vendors. 
Visit the Help Center to
 
learn how to add an international vendor
.
  
  
ADD A VENDOR
 
  
  
 
 
Looking for ways to streamline your financial operations? Your Customer Success Team is here to help you get the most out of BILL. Join one of our weekly webinars with live Q&A:
BILL 101
 (Tuesdays, 10 AM MT) – Learn the basics of setting up your account.
BILL 201
 (Wednesdays, 10 AM MT) – Dive into payment and vendor management.
Need quick support? For live support by chat or phone, visit our 
Help Center
.
  
 
 
Sync custom segments
No need to edit bills and transactions to match the fields you've set up in Oracle NetSuite. You can now automatically sync up to six custom segments between BILL and Oracle NetSuite for even more visibility and control over your financial data.
  
  
LEARN MORE
 
  
  
  
 
 
 
 
 
View as Webpage
   
Privacy Policy
   
Terms & Conditions
 
Bill.com, LLC • 6220 America Center Drive, San Jose, CA 95002
 
This email was sent to 
s.gluckstein@lcwmail.com
.

.

Hi,
We’re writing to let you know about an upcoming price adjustment.
What’s changing
The annual account fee will change from our legacy 0.08% to 0.15% effective on 5/1/2025. This fee is paid by participants to Guideline Investments, LLC.
Guideline remains one of the most affordable 401(k) providers available. Combined with low fund fees, the new pricing is up to 6x lower than the industry average
1
. This change does not affect any other fees, such as monthly base and per active participant fees.
New features
Guideline is committed to helping everyone arrive at a secure retirement. Be on the lookout for new upcoming features aimed at enhancing our saver experience, including after-tax savings, mega backdoor Roth, and expanded investment funds and vehicles.
How the annual account fee is calculated
Each month, on behalf of Guideline Investments, LLC, we’ll deduct 1/12 of the 0.15% account fee, which is based on a participant’s month-end account balance
2
.
For more information about how we calculate this fee and to view an example, 
see here
.
Where to learn more
To see more details, you can check out our 
pricing FAQ
. Your Service Agreement will be amended and your ERISA 408(b)(2) report for Guideline Investments, LLC will be updated to reflect this change. Your plan’s eligible, active, and dismissed participants with a balance will also receive notices in the coming weeks.
Team Guideline
Any questions?
View our 
FAQs
 to learn more about this update.
​
​
1. This information is provided for illustrative purposes only, and is not intended to be taken as investment or tax advice. Consult a qualified tax and financial advisor to determine the appropriate investment strategy for you. The average investment expense of plan assets for 401(k) plans with 25 participants and $250,000 in assets is 1.37% of assets, according to the 24th Edition of the 401k Averages Book, with data updated through September 30, 2023, and is inclusive of investment management fees, fund expense ratios, 12b-1 fees, sub-transfer agent fees, contract charges, wrap and advisor fees or any other asset based charges. Investment advisory services for Guideline’s 401(k) product (when 3(38) fiduciary services are appointed) and SEP IRA/IRA products are offered by Guideline Investments, LLC, an SEC-registered investment adviser. The managed portfolios have blended expense ratios ranging from 0.067% to 0.069% of assets under management. When combined with an assumed account fee of 0.15% charged by Guideline Investments, LLC, the estimated total AUM fees for one of the managed portfolios can be under 0.22%. Alternative account fee pricing is available ranging from 0.15% to 0.35%. Contact Sales at 
hello@guideline.com
 to learn more about exclusive pricing options available in the Enterprise tier. See the 
Form ADV 2A Brochure
 for more information regarding fees. Expense ratios for custom portfolios will vary. These expense ratios are subject to change by and paid to the fund(s). View 
full fund lineup
.
2. Information shown here assumes a static balance of $10,000 per month, an assumed annual account fee of 0.15% on assets under management (calculated and deducted on a monthly basis at 1/12 of the annual stated rate (0.15%) based on the month-end account balance) and does not account for common factors that affect the value of your account balance over time such as gains, losses, distributions, additional contributions, etc. It’s not intended to be taken as investment advice or as an assurance or guarantee of future performance. The fee presented does not include other fees that a 401(k) participant may incur from other third-parties or affiliates, including, but not limited to, from mutual fund expense ratios and a monthly maintenance fee to participants who end employment. Alternative account fee pricing is available, ranging from 0.15% to 0.35%. Contact Sales at 
hello@guideline.com
 to learn more about exclusive pricing options available in Enterprise tier.

subject: Question regarding next pay
body:
Hi Sarah, I hope you're well.
I wanted to ask if you could tell me when I can expect the next payment? I have a family emergency and I am trying to plan accordingly and having this information would help me. 
I also would like to change the bank account on the QuickBooks account. Is it too late for this next coming payment to deposit in the new account?
I appreciate your help on this matter.
Thank you!
Juri Mansour (She/Her)
Consultant Project Associate

subject: Important Action Needed -- April 30th Deadline for Your HR Services
body:
Dear Sarah
,
We value your business and want to follow up on an email you received last month about upcoming changes to your TriNet contract. As a reminder, TriNet will no longer offer month-to-month contracts. As your company is currently on a month-to-month contract, you need to take action and consider these following options:
Continue your relationship with TriNet
 by purchasing one of our new HR Plus annual contracts by April 30, 2025. To learn more about the new product offerings, click 
here
 or watch this on-demand 
webinar
.
Transition your HR services to GoCo by April 30, 2025,
 a leading industry provider of HCM solutions. GoCo is TriNet’s partner and has worked closely to match service offerings and pricing plans to the legacy retired TriNet plans. For more information about GoCo, visit the 
transition center
 to explore offerings, discuss your specific needs with a GoCo representative, and select a solution that best meets your needs. Please note, by clicking the link, you agree to TriNet forwarding your email address, current plan name, and company ID number to GoCo in order to expedite this process. For more information, please review GoCo’s 
privacy policy
.
For more information, TriNet and GoCo are hosting a webinar on March 13 at 12:30pm PST to highlight the product and migration process. 
Register here
.
Transition your HR services to a provider of your choice
 effective April 30, 2025. 
Please note, if no action is taken by April 30, 2025, your company’s month-to-month subscription will end, and your employees will be offboarded from TriNet as of May 1, 2025.
To learn more about the options above, or to inform us if you choose not to renew your account, click 
here
:
Select the Chat Bot in the bottom right-hand corner
Select “Click Here for Support”
Type "2025 plans and packages”
Click "Email Us"
We look forward to connecting with you.
Regards,
TriNet

Welcome to the TriNet HR Plus
Rollup Newsletter!
Last month TriNet introduced enhancements to our HR Plus solution, including updated packages. HR Plus is TriNet’s Administrative Services Organization (ASO) offering that pairs expert service with advanced technology for optimal impact. In this month’s newsletter we're excited to share more new features as well as content and events that support your business:
Explore Marketplace, TriNet’s new an all-in-one online digital destination with a curated network of business solutions, preferred pricing, and prebuilt integrations
Utilize our enhanced payroll experience
Leverage our Business Intelligence tool for your workforce analytics needs
Watch on-demand webinars about post-inauguration impact and our new HR Plus solution
And more!
See more updates
 
  
 
Introducing Marketplace!
TriNet’s Marketplace offers online access to business solutions with preferred pricing and pre-built integrations for your business’s needs, including Electric, Gifted, and more. Log in to TriNet HR Plus platform
(
https://secure.zenefits.com/accounts/login/
) and select the “Marketplace” tile on your dashboard to explore this curated network.
Explore now
 
  
Featured offers and integrations:
 
Get 20% off Hub Pro with Electric
Terms and conditions apply.
  
 
Full-service retirement plans with easy integration with TriNet.
Terms and conditions apply. 
  
 
50% Off All Access Plus plan with WeWork
Terms and conditions apply.
  
 
Enhanced Payroll
The new payroll experience on our HR platform is live! Start taking advantage of enhancements to help you process payroll more efficiently, including:
Quicker access to pay runs with new filter options
12-month calendar view with download and printing capabilities
Total hours paid displayed in gross-to-net Summary view
And more!
View demo
 
  
 
Leverage Business Intelligence Tool
for Workforce Analytics
The powerful capabilities of TriNet's 
Business Intelligence
 tool are designed to support and enhance your workforce analytics needs. Explore this 
interactive demo
 to help you leverage Business Intelligence to its full potential.
Explore demo
 
  
Suggested Resources
 
Post Inauguration Impact Webinar:
Preparing for the Year Ahead
Watch our on-demand webinar, "Post Inauguration Impact: Preparing for the Year Ahead," to learn about the potential HR impacts of the 2025 inauguration. Our experts discuss how new policies and regulations may affect small and medium-size businesses, covering compliance, employee benefits, and workplace trends.
Watch now
 
  
 
TriNet HR Plus Webinar:
Enhancing Your HR Experience
TriNet HR Platform clients can watch our on-demand webinar to learn about TriNet HR Plus, a reimagined solution for evolving business needs. Discover the changes, understand the reasons behind them, and get clear timelines for key decisions. Explore HR Plus packages, preview feature enhancements, and get practical advice to streamline operations and improve employee engagement. This session will help you make informed decisions and position your business for success in 2025 and beyond. 
View webinar

subject: We sued the Trump administration.  Here's how you can help:
body:
Dear 
Sarah
,
On February 19, AFC sued the Trump administration to block Trump’s executive orders banning federal funding from supporting work related to diversity, equity, inclusion, and accessibility, along with services to transgender individuals. We’re grateful to our pro bono lawyers at Lambda Legal and NAACP Legal Defense Fund for their incredible legal work.
Will you donate today to support AFC’s effort to push back against the Trump administration? Every dollar helps in the fight for fairness and equity!
The fact is, AFC must prioritize culturally competent work with Black, Latine, transgender, and broader LGBTQ+ communities because this is how we will end the HIV epidemic.  The epidemic is fueled by the same structural inequities that DEI work intends to dismantle. 
Training our staff to work within and across diverse communities, ensuring our workforce is diverse, prioritizing resources to reach the communities most impacted by HIV, and ensuring inclusive and accessible services for these communities are proven strategies to reduce transmission of HIV and increase quality of life for people living with HIV.
Our Policy & Advocacy team is working harder than ever before to push back against the Trump administration’s draconian policy pronouncements and efforts in Congress to slash the programs that people living with HIV rely on.
So, how can YOU help?
Show your support by making a gift to AFC today.  
Your donation supports the diverse communities and inclusive, equitable services essential to our fight to end the HIV epidemic.
Let's keep fighting together.
Give now
 
P.S. 
Read more about the lawsuit below in Lambda Legal’s press release and check us out in the news: 
Lambda Legal Press Release
New York Times 
Chicago Tribune

subject: Additional Security Steps Now Live for Updates to User Profiles on CitiBusiness® Online
body:
‌​Additional Security Steps Now Live for Updates to User Profiles on CitiBusiness® Online. As the fraud landscape evolves, we are continually working to introduce measures to help protect your accounts.  
  
  
‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌  
​
 
Additional Security Steps Now Live for Updates to User Profiles on CitiBusiness
®
 Online
As the fraud landscape evolves, we are continually working to introduce measures to help protect your accounts. As part of these efforts, from 
February 19, 2025
, every time you view or update your demographic information, such as your email address or phone number, you will be presented with a request to enter an additional One-Time-Password (OTP) authentication. The OTP will be sent to your verified phone number. If you do not have a verified phone number registered, the OTP will be sent to your verified primary email address.
System Administrators will also be required to pass the OTP verification step to update a user's information, or when adding a new user.
These OTP enhancements add another layer of security by requiring that anyone viewing, or editing, a user's personal information validates their identity through a verified phone number.
Did you know?
The 'Maker-Checker' process is a significant online control to guard against fraud and cyber-attacks. A robust maker/checker process introduces a second pair of eyes that can flag things that appear suspicious, strange, or incorrect. It can help protect your business, but it also helps protect your employees against error and unintended compromise.
If you opt-in to System Administration Maker-Checker on CitiBusiness Online you can bypass the OTP verification requirement, as all changes must be approved by the 'Checker'. Speak to your Citi Representative today to find out more about enrolling in System Administrator Maker-Checker.
What to do in the event of Fraud?
Act Quickly: Do not delay in notifying your bank about any suspected fraud. The shorter the time between a fraudulent transaction and detection, the greater the chance of recovery. Every minute counts.
Alert your banks and use the ‘F' Word: Be prepared to state that it is a Fraud.
Provide the details: Provide full transaction details and background details.
Independently secure your accounts to prevent further misuse
Alert all other banks that you hold accounts with
 
 
 
 
 
The Red Flags
Be suspicious of unsolicited phone calls from any individuals you do not know, even if they say they are calling from your bank.
Never share any passwords or token codes. Citi will never ask you to share this information.
Be suspicious if a caller is alarmist or aggressive in their request for you to approve a transaction or share your account details
Be wary of any requests to click on links in emails if you do not know the sender
Carefully review all invoices and any requests for changes to supplier details
 
 
 
 
​
Citi reminds you that Citi's clients are responsible for their organizations' cybersecurity and all matters relating thereto, and the information contained herein should not be viewed as any intention or commitment from Citi to replace your organization's cybersecurity-related responsibilities. Furthermore, although the information contained herein is believed to be reliable, the following does not constitute legal advice and Citi makes no representation or warranty as to the accuracy or completeness of any information contained herein or otherwise provided by it.

﻿
 
Hi everyone,
 
I chatted with Nicole yesterday about reducing my pay to help our cash situation, and I’m presenting the following proposal. Since I don’t work hourly, but rather by deliverable, I thought about a way to reduce my effort and time without cutting off critical deliverables. I determined that the best way to do this is to protect my time and streamline my responsibilities to accounting tasks only. I’m very invested in LCW’s success, so drawing some hard boundaries is the only way for me to be able to take the cut (otherwise I’ll just keep doing what I’ve been doing every day…)
 
New monthly fee: $2,500 (plus QBO fees billed through) - $1,000/month reduction
 
Reductions:
Less availability (4 days per week until 3 Central, typically Wednesdays off)
No support for mail or state regulatory items
 
Things that will remain the same:
Bank feed management in QBO as usual
AR management as usual, given current reduced volume (invoicing, following up, setup with clients)
AP management as usual (bill receiving, planning, processing, handling questions)
Payroll run approvals and JE's as usual
Weekly management reports as usual
Monthly JE's and reconciliations as usual
Collaboration with auditor and tax preparers as usual
Closing last year as usual
Team meetings as usual
Other accounting-related requests 
as time allows
 (pulling reports, spreadsheet updates, etc)
 
I’m willing to backdate this change to February 1
st
, since we’re so early in the month. Since you’ve already paid me for February, I’d take the extra $1,000 off my March invoice.
 
“SG” Gluckstein

Hi everyone,
 
I chatted with Nicole yesterday about reducing my pay to help our cash situation, and I’m presenting the following proposal. Since I don’t work hourly, but rather by deliverable, I thought about a way to reduce my effort and time without cutting off critical deliverables. I determined that the best way to do this is to protect my time and streamline my responsibilities to accounting tasks only. I’m very invested in LCW’s success, so drawing some hard boundaries is the only way for me to be able to take the cut (otherwise I’ll just keep doing what I’ve been doing every day…)
 
New monthly fee: $2,500 (plus QBO fees billed through) - $1,000/month reduction
 
Reductions:
Less availability (4 days per week until 3 Central, typically Wednesdays off)
No support for mail or state regulatory items
 
Things that will remain the same:
Bank feed management in QBO as usual
AR management as usual, given current reduced volume (invoicing, following up, setup with clients)
AP management as usual (bill receiving, planning, processing, handling questions)
Payroll run approvals and JE's as usual
Weekly management reports as usual
Monthly JE's and reconciliations as usual
Collaboration with auditor and tax preparers as usual
Closing last year as usual
Team meetings as usual
Other accounting-related requests 
as time allows
 (pulling reports, spreadsheet updates, etc)
 
I’m willing to backdate this change to February 1
st
, since we’re so early in the month. Since you’ve already paid me for February, I’d take the extra $1,000 off my March invoice.
 
“SG” Gluckstein

subject: 2024 ACA Filing Deadlines Approaching
body:
Dear Valued Client
,
As a reminder, you can access Forms 1094-C and 1095-C to complete your 2024 Affordable Care Act (ACA) filing* requirements. To generate the forms, visit the ACA Compliance app on the TriNet platform (
TriNet.com/login
) and click the “Filing” tab in the top navigation. If you haven’t added the ACA Compliance app to your current subscription, please contact your Customer Relationship Manager or email 
Tz-Renewal_Specialists-SF@Trinet.com
 to begin setup.
After generating the forms, choose how you will send Form 1095-C to your employees and select your filing method. If filing 10 or more forms for 2024, you are required to file them with the IRS electronically. Please note the following deadlines:
February 21, 2025:
 Submit Form 1095-C for TriNet review prior to employee distribution.
February 28, 2025:
 IRS deadline for paper filing.
March 3, 2025:
 IRS deadline to provide Form1095-C to employees. 
March 21, 2025:
 Submit IRS filings through the TriNet platform (
TriNet.com/login
). Failure to submit by this date may result in delayed review and processing.
March 31, 2025:
 IRS deadline for electronic filing.
Please note, you can also download Form 1095-C for terminated employees. See 
this article
 for how to pull a report to mail Form 1095-C to a terminated employees’ last known address.
To review your filing submission status, click the “Filing” tab in the top navigation of the ACA Compliance app. If the status is “Accepted with Errors” or “Rejected,” you’ll need to fix the errors or submit corrections as soon as possible.
For information on how to fix the 
most common ACA-related errors
 in the ACA Compliance app, please review the following:
How do I fix business control code for ACA e-filing?
How do I fix individual control code for ACA e-filing?
What happens if my company can’t fix the ACA e-filing errors?
If you have any questions, reach out to our 
Customer Support team
.
Regards,
TriNet
*ACA filing is required for companies that qualify as an 
Applicable Large Employer
 (ALE) or are part of an Aggregated Applicable Large Employer (AALE).

Hi everyone,
 
I chatted with Nicole yesterday about reducing my pay to help our cash situation, and I’m presenting the following proposal. Since I don’t work hourly, but rather by deliverable, I thought about a way to reduce my effort and time without cutting off critical deliverables. I determined that the best way to do this is to protect my time and streamline my responsibilities to accounting tasks only. I’m very invested in LCW’s success, so drawing some hard boundaries is the only way for me to be able to take the cut (otherwise I’ll just keep doing what I’ve been doing every day…)
 
New monthly fee: $2,500 (plus QBO fees billed through) - $1,000/month reduction
 
Reductions:
Less availability (4 days per week until 3 Central, typically Wednesdays off)
No support for mail or state regulatory items
 
Things that will remain the same:
Bank feed management in QBO as usual
AR management as usual, given current reduced volume (invoicing, following up, setup with clients)

Payroll run approvals and JE's as usual
Weekly management reports as usual
Monthly JE's and reconciliations as usual
Collaboration with auditor and tax preparers as usual
Closing last year as usual
Team meetings as usual
Other accounting-related requests 
as time allows
 (pulling reports, spreadsheet updates, etc)
 
I’m willing to backdate this change to February 1
st

subject: Larry Baker Will be Terminated from Language & Culture Worldwide on February 14th, 2025
body:
We've received your request to terminate Larry Baker on 02/14/2025. Don't worry, we won't send them any communication. 
Here's what TriNet will take care of:
Payroll: We'll mark Larry for termination in payroll on 
02/14/2025
, and continue to pay them unless you manually remove them. Issue their last pay check by running termination payroll. 
Not sure how? 
We recommend you understand 
your state's specific final paycheck requirements 
to remain compliant with the law. 
Here's what you need to take care of:
 
Final Payment: Each state has a different law regarding when a company must give terminated employees their final paychecks. Please refer to the Final Paycheck law for IL to find out when you have cut this employee's final paycheck. We recommend that you confirm the final amount you owe Larry with your payroll provider before cutting the check. 
Termination & Severance Paperwork: If your company uses any termination forms, you'll want to get the individual to sign them and you'll want to 
add the signed documents here
 for future reference. 
If you have any questions or concerns feel free to 
contact us.
 
Thanks,
TriNet

help.zenefits.com
.

Dear Sarah,
 
Just a friendly reminder about our upcoming exclusive webinar for TriNet HR Platform and HR Plus clients! Don't forget to join us on Tuesday, January 28, 2025, at 2 p.m. ET / 11 a.m. PT for 
TriNet HR Plus: Enhancing Your HR Experience
. This event will showcase the enhanced HR Plus, a reimagined solution designed to meet the evolving needs of your business.
 
TriNet HR Plus: 
Enhancing Your HR Experience
Tuesday, January 28, 2025
 at 2 p.m. ET / 11 a.m. PT.
Register Now
 
  
What You’ll Gain from Attending
Understand the Changes:
 Discover what’s changing for HR Platform clients, the reasons behind the change, and how these updates align with your needs. 
Plan Ahead:
 Get clear timelines for key decisions, so you know exactly what to expect and when. 
Explore HR Plus:
 Get an overview of HR Plus packages, designed to offer robust support, scalable solutions, and enhanced technology.
Preview Enhancements:
 Hear about key feature enhancements designed to streamline operations, improve employee engagement, and provide greater value.
 
This session will ensure you have the information needed to help make an informed decision about TriNet HR Plus. Don’t miss this opportunity to elevate your HR strategy and position your business for success in 2025 and beyond. 
 
We look forward to your participation!
 
Regards,
TriNet

subject: Pedro Seminario Will be Terminated from Language & Culture Worldwide on January 21st, 2025
body:
We've received your request to terminate Pedro Seminario on 01/21/2025. Don't worry, we won't send them any communication. 
Here's what TriNet will take care of:
Payroll: We'll remove Pedro from your payroll, and they will not be paid going forward (unless you choose to manually mark them as "active"). 
COBRA: COBRA Complete is administering COBRA for Pedro Seminario. TriNet will send Pedro's information to COBRA Complete within 24 hours after the termination date. If you have any questions, please email COBRAComplete@healthaccountservices.com. 
Here's what you need to take care of:
 
Final Payment: Each state has a different law regarding when a company must give terminated employees their final paychecks. Please refer to the Final Paycheck law for NJ to find out when you have cut this employee's final paycheck. We recommend that you confirm the final amount you owe Pedro with your payroll provider before cutting the check. 
Termination & Severance Paperwork: If your company uses any termination forms, you'll want to get the individual to sign them and you'll want to 
add the signed documents here
 for future reference. 
If you have any questions or concerns feel free to 
contact us.
 
Thanks,
TriNet
For more information or assistance, please visit 
help.zenefits.com
.

subject: 2024 ACA Filing Now Available
body:
Dear Valued Client
,
You can now access Forms 1094-C and 1095-C to complete your 2024 Affordable Care Act (ACA) filing* requirements. To generate the forms, visit the ACA Compliance app on the TriNet platform (
TriNet.com/login
) and click the “Filing” tab in the top navigation. 
After generating the forms, choose how you will send Form 1095-C to your employees and select your filing method. If filing 10 or more forms for 2024, you are required to file them electronically. Please note the following deadlines: 
February 21, 2025:
 Submit Form 1095-C for TriNet review prior to employee distribution.
February 28, 2025:
 IRS deadline for paper filing.
March 3, 2025:
 IRS deadline to provide Forms 1095-C to employees. 
March 21, 2025:
 Submit IRS filings through the TriNet platform (
TriNet.com/login
). Failure to submit by this date may result in delayed review and processing.
March 31, 2025:
 IRS deadline for electronic filing.
If you have any questions, reach out to our 
Customer Support team
.
Regards,
TriNet
*ACA filing is required for companies that qualify as an 
Applicable Large Employer
 (ALE) or are part of an Aggregated Applicable Large Employer (AALE).

subject: Enhanced HR Plus Offering Provides Exceptional Service Enabled by Advanced Technology to Benefit Your Business
body:
Dear Sarah,
We are excited to announce the availability of a new enhanced HR Plus Administrative Services Organization (ASO) solution. This new offering provides an intuitive all-in-one service package enabled by technology designed to simplify and optimize HR payroll and benefits administration into one complete package to support you and your business. 
Join us for an informative webinar on January 28, 2025, where we'll explore the enhanced HR Plus offering. 
Sign up here!
 In the meantime, explore our new ASO packages 
here
.
Important Update - Your TriNet Contract
We are committed to providing the best service possible and have updated our contract options. Moving forward, TriNet will no longer offer month-to-month contracts. Since your company is currently on a month-to-month contract, we’d like to offer you a few options to consider:
Purchase one of our new annual HR Plus packages by April 30, 2025. Click 
here
 to explore. 
-OR-
TriNet has partnered with GoCo to provide our HCM SaaS clients an option if they do not choose to upgrade to our enhanced HR Plus portfolio of services. GoCo is a leading industry provider of HCM solutions and has worked to closely match their service offerings and pricing plans to the legacy TriNet plans that will be discontinued. They have set up a transition center that will allow you to explore their offerings, discuss your specific needs with a GoCo representative, and select a solution that best meets your needs. We will work with them to provide an efficient offboarding from TriNet and transition to their platform. To learn more, please click 
here
. Please note, by clicking the link, you agree to TriNet forwarding your email address, current plan name, and company ID number to GoCo in order to expedite this process. For more information, please review GoCo’s 
privacy policy
.
We value your business and are here to help make this change as seamless as possible.
To learn more about the options above, or to not renew your account, click 
here
:
Select the Chat Bot in the bottom right-hand corner 
Select “Click Here for Support”
Type "2025 plans and packages”
Click "Email Us"
Please note, if no action is taken by April 30, 2025, your company’s month-to-month subscription will end, and employees will be offboarded from TriNet completely as of May 1, 2025.
HR Plus Access and Features
Our new HR Plus Advisory package includes our full suite of technology: Advisory Services, Performance Management, Learning Management, Business Intelligence, Employee Engagement Surveys, People Hub, Payroll, Benefits and COBRA Administration, ACA tool, and more!
We will continue offering optional add-ons, including EDI ($2/employee/month), international worker and contingent worker management ($6/worker/month), and JazzHR, with the same functionality under new package names and pricing. 
Updates to Fees and Products
Great news! With the introduction of our new HR Plus offerings, TriNet has removed some of our one-off fees. Once on a new HR Plus package, TriNet will no longer charge the standard employer and annual set up fees for HSA, Commuter and FSA accounts. Additionally, the TriNet processing fees historically associated with Reverse Wire transactions will no longer be charged (your bank fees may still apply). You will also continue to have access to robust workforce analytics and compensation management features: 
Our 
Business Intelligence
 tool supports and enhances your workforce analytics needs and helps you make data-driven decisions. Check out this 
interactive demo
 to help you leverage Business Intelligence to its full potential. We are retiring People Analytics, powered by Visier, on January 31, 2025.
To support your compensation management needs, the HR Library includes a built-in compensation benchmarking tool. This can enable you to make better informed compensation decisions. You can find the compensation benchmarking tool by navigating to the HR Library tile in the HR platform > select Manage in HR Library > Continue to Zywave > HR apps > Salary Benchmarking. Additionally, we are excited to announce new offerings from Salary.com that will soon be featured in our Marketplace. Marketplace offers a thoughtfully curated network of business solutions for clients, featuring preferred pricing and easily accessible prebuilt integrations for select solutions. We are retiring the Compensation Management feature on January 31, 2025. 
Regards, 
TriNet

body:
We've received your request to terminate Sarah Nodarse on 01/31/2025. Don't worry, we won't send them any communication.

Payroll: We'll mark Sarah for termination in payroll on 
01/31/2025
, and continue to pay them unless you manually remove them. Issue their last pay check by running termination payroll.

your state's specific final paycheck requirements

Final Payment: Each state has a different law regarding when a company must give terminated employees their final paychecks. January Newsletter
 
Hello Alisa, 
Happy New Year! Thank you to everyone who helped with or participated in programs and initiatives in 2024. We are planning exciting things for 2025 and hope you can make one of our upcoming events! 
In this newsletter: 
Check out upcoming Happy Hour events around the country
Look at this: Launching in L.A.!
Community Corner
 
 
Upcoming Events!
 
 
Atlanta New Year Happy Hour
Thursday, January 16 | 5:30-7:30 pm ET
Atlanta, GA
Out in Finance is excited to bring our Atlanta members together for drinks at Blake's on the Park!
Networking doesn't get easier - join fellow members, colleagues, and friends over free drinks and bar bites. This event is the perfect event to catch up, meet new people, and expand your professional network.
This event is FREE to attend, but space is limited, so be sure to RSVP as soon as possible.
 
RSVP
 
 
 
Chicago New Year Happy Hour
Thursday, January 16 | 6-8 pm CT
Chicago, IL
Atlanta isn't the only Happy Hour on the block on January 16. Chicago members are welcome to join one another for our annual networking and happy hour at Sidetrack on the same evening! 
This event is FREE to attend, but space is limited, so be sure to RSVP and secure your spot.
 
RSVP
 
 
 
Boston New Year Happy Hour
Thursday, January 23 | 6-8 pm ET
Boston, MA
Kick off the New Year and join Boston members for drinks at The Kartal in the South End! Make this the year you resolve to network, make new friends, or find that new profession. Join us to meet others and make your 2025 goals come true!
As with all of our programming, the event is FREE to attend, but space is limited. RSVP to secure your spot. 
 
RSVP
 
 
 
Los Angeles Launch!
 
 
Los Angeles Launch Event
Thursday, February 27 | 6-8 pm PT
West Hollywood, CA
Our hearts are with the Los Angeles community as they face the challenges of the ongoing wildfires affecting the region. We encourage you to find resources and ways to support those impacted through the 
Los Angeles LGBT Center
. 
We’re excited to invite LGBTQ+ and allied financial professionals to an exclusive evening to foster and build connection and create an environment of opportunity.
Join us for complimentary drinks and snacks as you expand your professional network and forge meaningful connections within the financial services industry.
As always, this event is 
completely free
, but space is limited—don’t wait! RSVP now to secure your spot and be part of an unforgettable evening.
 
RSVP
 
 
 
Share that Good News!
 
We want to celebrate your recent achievements! Whether you’ve stepped into an exciting promotion, embraced a new role, or embarked on a fresh career path, we are here to cheer you on. We also want to take a moment to recognize your fantastic milestones, like work anniversaries and the successful completion of big projects and exams. If you've hit any professional targets recently, we are eager to showcase examples of LGBTQ+ success and share it with our active 
LinkedIn community
. 
  
 
Share Good News

subject: Declined: Weekly Accounting Chat
body: Thanks for the voice note. I think it best to do voice notes for Monday’s going forward and if you need a call, please schedule it. Then let’s do an end of week call on Fridays to discuss new implementations and etc? We are focusing on restructuring and I want to make sure we have the capacity. Friday’s will be the call to arrange work for the upcoming week as well. If you disagree, please let me know and thoughts.
